title: Everly Brothers - australia 1971
description:
The Everly Brothers resumed performing in 1971, and signed a contract with RCA.
Their world tour included Australia, Europe, USA, and Canada. On August 20th 1971
at the Capital Theatre Sydney, Australia, the Everly Brothers performed a live
TV concert, which was recorded on videotape by ABC TV. Phil Everly was also
interviewed before the concert. This TV recording is a rare snapshot of the Everly
Brothers performing live in the early 1970s.
